race.comment: KING JERRY (3) settled last in a big field at Rosehill in stronger and didn't do a bad job beaten less than 3L over 1500m. Just missed a place in a 64 at Newcastle prior and that reads well. Finds the right race and will go close.  SAINTLY SANDS (8) brings a string of narrow country defeats and has a key gear switch. Was heavily bet last time over this distance and will be finishing hard. INCEPTION (2) peaks and is better placed today. Has a wide barrier but Morgan is a key jockey switch replacing the 3kg apprentice. Capable of featuring at best. The gun hoop is booked for DOWN THE KOOKA (1) and that demands attention. Has the rail and presents off a narrow defeat at Dubbo this grade/trip.
